From: Shawn Guo <shawn.guo@freescale.com>
Date: Sun, 14 Jul 2013 21:10:37 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 0968/1072] ENGR00269945: reset: build in CONFIG_RESET_GPIO by
 default

git://git.freescale.com/imx/linux-2.6-imx.git imx_3.10.17_1.0.0_beta
commit b61ee544c878df69cd2e512f4b769d54e939e5af

GPIO is widely used as the reset control for various devices.  Let's
build the support in by default.

Signed-off-by: Shawn Guo <shawn.guo@freescale.com>
Signed-off-by: Hongbo Zhong <hongbo.zhong@windriver.com>
---
 drivers/reset/Kconfig |    1 +
 1 files changed, 1 insertions(+), 0 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/reset/Kconfig b/drivers/reset/Kconfig
index a7e6022..6fec851 100644
--- a/drivers/reset/Kconfig
+++ b/drivers/reset/Kconfig
@@ -26,6 +26,7 @@ config	RESET_TI
 
 config RESET_GPIO
 	tristate "GPIO reset controller support"
+	default y
 	depends on GPIOLIB && OF
 	help
 	  This driver provides support for reset lines that are controlled
